Lindani Myeni was shot by the police in Hawaii in he US (Screenshot) JOHANNESBURG - Lindani Myeni's body is expected back in South Africa on Friday. The former rugby player was shot and killed by police in Hawaii. The officers were called following an alleged burglary. READ: Lindani Myeni's family to open wrongful death suit Circumstances around Myeni's death remain sketchy. That's despite footage from body cameras worn by the police documenting the incident Myeni's family is pursuing a lawsuit against authorities for wrongful death.